                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 738.3915/113.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister to Haiti</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 6, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>General Zamor at Cape Haitien telegraphs that Dominican troops have again crossed
                    the frontier near Ouanaminthe and are fighting and devastating the country. As
                    this is the second time recently that Dominican troops have invaded Haitian
                    territory, the Haitian Government now contemplates vigorous measures. From the
                    attitude of the Dominican Government as expressed to me by the Dominican
                    Minister it appears that the invasion is intended to bring about a clash between
                    the two countries.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Furniss.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
